FBIS3-658 "drafr048_c_94021" FBIS-AFR-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Violence Descends on Bophuthatswana as Government Flees Security Chiefs Hold Talks MB1103145494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 11 Mar 94 MB1103145494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The commissioner of the South African Police, General Johan van der Merwe, and the South African Defense Force Chief, General George Meiring, are in the [Bophuthatswana] homeland to hold talks with the government of Bophuthatswana. A police spokesman said the possibility of sending in the South African Police to bring the situation under control will be discussed.
